olive oil
1 packet spaghetti
1 tomato
1 packet Soffritto Mix
2 packet beef mince
1 packet tomato paste
1 packet garlic paste
1 sachet Classic Roast Seasoning
1 packet Red Wine Jus
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet Rocket leaves
drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Half-fill a large saucepan with water, add a generous pinch of salt, then bring to the boil over high heat.
• Cook spaghetti in boiling water until ‘al dente’, 10 minutes. Reserve some pasta water (1/2 cup for 2 people/1 cup for 4 people). Drain and return to the saucepan.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop tomato.
• In a large frying pan heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook soffritto mix, and cook until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Add beef mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.

• Reduce heat to medium, the stir through tomato paste, garlic paste and Aussie spice blend until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add red wine jus, chicken-style stock powder, brown sugar and reserved pasta water and cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add cooked spaghetti and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.
TIP: Add a splash more pasta water to your sauce if it's looking dry!

• In a medium bowl, combine rocket leaves, tomato, a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil. Season.
• Divide red wine beef ragu spaghetti between bowls. Top with grated Parmesan cheese. Serve with tomato and rocket salad. Enjoy!